342static bool shouldKeep(object::SectionRef S) {
343 if (FilterSections.empty())
344 return true;
345 StringRef String;
346 std::error_code error = S.getName(String);
347 if (error)
348 return false;
349 return is_contained(FilterSections, String);
350}
351
352SectionFilter ToolSectionFilter(object::ObjectFile const &O) {
353 return SectionFilter([](object::SectionRef S) { return shouldKeep(S); }, O);
354}

356void error(std::error_code EC) {
357 if (!EC)
358 return;
359 WithColor::error(errs(), ToolName)
360 << "reading file: " << EC.message() << ".\n";
361 errs().flush();
362 exit(1);
363}
364
365void error(Error E) {
366 if (!E)
367 return;
368 WithColor::error(errs(), ToolName) << toString(std::move(E));
369 exit(1);
370}

387LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_NORETURN void report_error(StringRef File, Twine Message) {
388 WithColor::error(errs(), ToolName)
389 << "'" << File << "': " << Message << ".\n";
390 exit(1);
391}
392
393LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_NORETURN void report_error(Error E, StringRef File) {
394 assert(E);
395 std::string Buf;
396 raw_string_ostream OS(Buf);
397 logAllUnhandledErrors(std::move(E), OS);
398 OS.flush();
399 WithColor::error(errs(), ToolName) << "'" << File << "': " << Buf;
400 exit(1);
401}
402
403LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_NORETURN void report_error(Error E, StringRef ArchiveName,
404 StringRef FileName,
405 StringRef ArchitectureName) {
406 assert(E);
407 WithColor::error(errs(), ToolName);
408 if (ArchiveName != "")
409 errs() << ArchiveName << "(" << FileName << ")";
410 else
411 errs() << "'" << FileName << "'";
412 if (!ArchitectureName.empty())
413 errs() << " (for architecture " << ArchitectureName << ")";
414 std::string Buf;
415 raw_string_ostream OS(Buf);
416 logAllUnhandledErrors(std::move(E), OS);
417 OS.flush();
418 errs() << ": " << Buf;
419 exit(1);
420}
421
422LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_NORETURN void report_error(Error E, StringRef ArchiveName,
423 const object::Archive::Child &C,
424 StringRef ArchitectureName) {
425 Expected<StringRef> NameOrErr = C.getName();
426 // TODO: if we have a error getting the name then it would be nice to print
427 // the index of which archive member this is and or its offset in the
428 // archive instead of "???" as the name.
429 if (!NameOrErr) {
430 consumeError(NameOrErr.takeError());
431 report_error(std::move(E), ArchiveName, "???", ArchitectureName);
432 } else
433 report_error(std::move(E), ArchiveName, NameOrErr.get(), ArchitectureName);
434}

436static const Target *getTarget(const ObjectFile *Obj = nullptr) {
437 // Figure out the target triple.
438 Triple TheTriple("unknown-unknown-unknown");
439 if (TripleName.empty()) {
440 if (Obj)
441 TheTriple = Obj->makeTriple();
442 } else {
443 TheTriple.setTriple(Triple::normalize(TripleName));
444
445 // Use the triple, but also try to combine with ARM build attributes.
446 if (Obj) {
447 auto Arch = Obj->getArch();
448 if (Arch == Triple::arm || Arch == Triple::armeb)
449 Obj->setARMSubArch(TheTriple);
450 }
451 }
452
453 // Get the target specific parser.
454 std::string Error;
455 const Target *TheTarget = TargetRegistry::lookupTarget(ArchName, TheTriple,
456 Error);
457 if (!TheTarget) {
458 if (Obj)
459 report_error(Obj->getFileName(), "can't find target: " + Error);
460 else
461 error("can't find target: " + Error);
462 }
463
464 // Update the triple name and return the found target.
465 TripleName = TheTriple.getTriple();
466 return TheTarget;
467}

469bool isRelocAddressLess(RelocationRef A, RelocationRef B) {
470 return A.getOffset() < B.getOffset();
471}
472
473static Error getRelocationValueString(const RelocationRef &Rel,
474 SmallVectorImpl<char> &Result) {
475 const ObjectFile *Obj = Rel.getObject();
476 if (auto *ELF = dyn_cast<ELFObjectFileBase>(Obj))
477 return getELFRelocationValueString(ELF, Rel, Result);
478 if (auto *COFF = dyn_cast<COFFObjectFile>(Obj))
479 return getCOFFRelocationValueString(COFF, Rel, Result);
480 if (auto *Wasm = dyn_cast<WasmObjectFile>(Obj))
481 return getWasmRelocationValueString(Wasm, Rel, Result);
482 if (auto *MachO = dyn_cast<MachOObjectFile>(Obj))
483 return getMachORelocationValueString(MachO, Rel, Result);
484 llvm_unreachable("unknown object file format");
485}
486
487/// Indicates whether this relocation should hidden when listing
488/// relocations, usually because it is the trailing part of a multipart
489/// relocation that will be printed as part of the leading relocation.
490static bool getHidden(RelocationRef RelRef) {
491 auto *MachO = dyn_cast<MachOObjectFile>(RelRef.getObject());
492 if (!MachO)
493 return false;
494
495 unsigned Arch = MachO->getArch();
496 DataRefImpl Rel = RelRef.getRawDataRefImpl();
497 uint64_t Type = MachO->getRelocationType(Rel);
498
499 // On arches that use the generic relocations, GENERIC_RELOC_PAIR
500 // is always hidden.
501 if (Arch == Triple::x86 || Arch == Triple::arm || Arch == Triple::ppc)
502 return Type == MachO::GENERIC_RELOC_PAIR;
503
504 if (Arch == Triple::x86_64) {
505 // On x86_64, X86_64_RELOC_UNSIGNED is hidden only when it follows
506 // an X86_64_RELOC_SUBTRACTOR.
507 if (Type == MachO::X86_64_RELOC_UNSIGNED && Rel.d.a > 0) {
508 DataRefImpl RelPrev = Rel;
509 RelPrev.d.a--;
510 uint64_t PrevType = MachO->getRelocationType(RelPrev);
511 if (PrevType == MachO::X86_64_RELOC_SUBTRACTOR)
512 return true;
513 }
514 }
515
516 return false;
517}

519namespace {
520class SourcePrinter {
521protected:
522 DILineInfo OldLineInfo;
523 const ObjectFile *Obj = nullptr;
524 std::unique_ptr<symbolize::LLVMSymbolizer> Symbolizer;
525 // File name to file contents of source
526 std::unordered_map<std::string, std::unique_ptr<MemoryBuffer>> SourceCache;
527 // Mark the line endings of the cached source
528 std::unordered_map<std::string, std::vector<StringRef>> LineCache;
529
530private:
531 bool cacheSource(const DILineInfo& LineInfoFile);
532
533public:
534 SourcePrinter() = default;
535 SourcePrinter(const ObjectFile *Obj, StringRef DefaultArch) : Obj(Obj) {
536 symbolize::LLVMSymbolizer::Options SymbolizerOpts;
537 SymbolizerOpts.PrintFunctions = DILineInfoSpecifier::FunctionNameKind::None;
538 SymbolizerOpts.Demangle = false;
539 SymbolizerOpts.DefaultArch = DefaultArch;
540 Symbolizer.reset(new symbolize::LLVMSymbolizer(SymbolizerOpts));
541 }
542 virtual ~SourcePrinter() = default;
543 virtual void printSourceLine(raw_ostream &OS,
544 object::SectionedAddress Address,
545 StringRef Delimiter = "; ");
546};
547
548bool SourcePrinter::cacheSource(const DILineInfo &LineInfo) {
549 std::unique_ptr<MemoryBuffer> Buffer;
550 if (LineInfo.Source) {
551 Buffer = MemoryBuffer::getMemBuffer(*LineInfo.Source);
552 } else {
553 auto BufferOrError = MemoryBuffer::getFile(LineInfo.FileName);
554 if (!BufferOrError)
555 return false;
556 Buffer = std::move(*BufferOrError);
557 }
558 // Chomp the file to get lines
559 const char *BufferStart = Buffer->getBufferStart(),
560 *BufferEnd = Buffer->getBufferEnd();
561 std::vector<StringRef> &Lines = LineCache[LineInfo.FileName];
562 const char *Start = BufferStart;
563 for (const char *I = BufferStart; I != BufferEnd; ++I)
564 if (*I == '\n') {
565 Lines.emplace_back(Start, I - Start - (BufferStart < I && I[-1] == '\r'));
566 Start = I + 1;
567 }
568 if (Start < BufferEnd)
569 Lines.emplace_back(Start, BufferEnd - Start);
570 SourceCache[LineInfo.FileName] = std::move(Buffer);
571 return true;
572}
573
574void SourcePrinter::printSourceLine(raw_ostream &OS,
575 object::SectionedAddress Address,
576 StringRef Delimiter) {
577 if (!Symbolizer)
578 return;
579 DILineInfo LineInfo = DILineInfo();
580 auto ExpectedLineInfo =
581 Symbolizer->symbolizeCode(Obj->getFileName(), Address);
582 if (!ExpectedLineInfo)
583 consumeError(ExpectedLineInfo.takeError());
584 else
585 LineInfo = *ExpectedLineInfo;
586
587 if ((LineInfo.FileName == "<invalid>") || LineInfo.Line == 0 ||
588 ((OldLineInfo.Line == LineInfo.Line) &&
589 (OldLineInfo.FileName == LineInfo.FileName)))
590 return;
591
592 if (PrintLines)
593 OS << Delimiter << LineInfo.FileName << ":" << LineInfo.Line << "\n";
594 if (PrintSource) {
595 if (SourceCache.find(LineInfo.FileName) == SourceCache.end())
596 if (!cacheSource(LineInfo))
597 return;
598 auto LineBuffer = LineCache.find(LineInfo.FileName);
599 if (LineBuffer != LineCache.end()) {
600 if (LineInfo.Line > LineBuffer->second.size())
601 return;
602 // Vector begins at 0, line numbers are non-zero
603 OS << Delimiter << LineBuffer->second[LineInfo.Line - 1] << '\n';
604 }
605 }
606 OldLineInfo = LineInfo;
607}

609static bool isArmElf(const ObjectFile *Obj) {
610 return (Obj->isELF() &&
611 (Obj->getArch() == Triple::aarch64 ||
612 Obj->getArch() == Triple::aarch64_be ||
613 Obj->getArch() == Triple::arm || Obj->getArch() == Triple::armeb ||
614 Obj->getArch() == Triple::thumb ||
615 Obj->getArch() == Triple::thumbeb));
616}
617
618static void printRelocation(const RelocationRef &Rel, uint64_t Address,
619 uint8_t AddrSize) {
620 StringRef Fmt =
621 AddrSize > 4 ? "\t\t%016" PRIx64 ": " : "\t\t\t%08" PRIx64 ": ";
622 SmallString<16> Name;
623 SmallString<32> Val;
624 Rel.getTypeName(Name);
625 error(getRelocationValueString(Rel, Val));
626 outs() << format(Fmt.data(), Address) << Name << "\t" << Val << "\n";
627}
628
629class PrettyPrinter {
630public:
631 virtual ~PrettyPrinter() = default;
632 virtual void printInst(MCInstPrinter &IP, const MCInst *MI,
633 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Bytes,
634 object::SectionedAddress Address, raw_ostream &OS,
635 StringRef Annot, MCSubtargetInfo const &STI,
636 SourcePrinter *SP,
637 std::vector<RelocationRef> *Rels = nullptr) {
638 if (SP && (PrintSource || PrintLines))
639 SP->printSourceLine(OS, Address);
640
641 {
642 formatted_raw_ostream FOS(OS);
643 if (!NoLeadingAddr)
644 FOS << format("%8" PRIx64 ":", Address.Address);
645 if (!NoShowRawInsn) {
646 FOS << ' ';
647 dumpBytes(Bytes, FOS);
648 }
649 FOS.flush();
650 // The output of printInst starts with a tab. Print some spaces so that
651 // the tab has 1 column and advances to the target tab stop.
652 unsigned TabStop = NoShowRawInsn ? 16 : 40;
653 unsigned Column = FOS.getColumn();
654 FOS.indent(Column < TabStop - 1 ? TabStop - 1 - Column : 7 - Column % 8);
655
656 // The dtor calls flush() to ensure the indent comes before printInst().
657 }
658
659 if (MI)
660 IP.printInst(MI, OS, "", STI);
661 else
662 OS << "\t<unknown>";
663 }
664};
665PrettyPrinter PrettyPrinterInst;
666class HexagonPrettyPrinter : public PrettyPrinter {
667public:
668 void printLead(ArrayRef<uint8_t> Bytes, uint64_t Address,
669 raw_ostream &OS) {
670 uint32_t opcode =
671 (Bytes[3] << 24) | (Bytes[2] << 16) | (Bytes[1] << 8) | Bytes[0];
672 if (!NoLeadingAddr)
673 OS << format("%8" PRIx64 ":", Address);
674 if (!NoShowRawInsn) {
675 OS << "\t";
676 dumpBytes(Bytes.slice(0, 4), OS);
677 OS << format("\t%08" PRIx32, opcode);
678 }
679 }
680 void printInst(MCInstPrinter &IP, const MCInst *MI, ArrayRef<uint8_t> Bytes,
681 object::SectionedAddress Address, raw_ostream &OS,
682 StringRef Annot, MCSubtargetInfo const &STI, SourcePrinter *SP,
683 std::vector<RelocationRef> *Rels) override {
684 if (SP && (PrintSource || PrintLines))
685 SP->printSourceLine(OS, Address, "");
686 if (!MI) {
687 printLead(Bytes, Address.Address, OS);
688 OS << " <unknown>";
689 return;
690 }
691 std::string Buffer;
692 {
693 raw_string_ostream TempStream(Buffer);
694 IP.printInst(MI, TempStream, "", STI);
695 }
696 StringRef Contents(Buffer);
697 // Split off bundle attributes
698 auto PacketBundle = Contents.rsplit('\n');
699 // Split off first instruction from the rest
700 auto HeadTail = PacketBundle.first.split('\n');
701 auto Preamble = " { ";
702 auto Separator = "";
703
704 // Hexagon's packets require relocations to be inline rather than
705 // clustered at the end of the packet.
706 std::vector<RelocationRef>::const_iterator RelCur = Rels->begin();
707 std::vector<RelocationRef>::const_iterator RelEnd = Rels->end();
708 auto PrintReloc = [&]() -> void {
709 while ((RelCur != RelEnd) && (RelCur->getOffset() <= Address.Address)) {
710 if (RelCur->getOffset() == Address.Address) {
711 printRelocation(*RelCur, Address.Address, 4);
712 return;
713 }
714 ++RelCur;
715 }
716 };
717
718 while (!HeadTail.first.empty()) {
719 OS << Separator;
720 Separator = "\n";
721 if (SP && (PrintSource || PrintLines))
722 SP->printSourceLine(OS, Address, "");
723 printLead(Bytes, Address.Address, OS);
724 OS << Preamble;
725 Preamble = " ";
726 StringRef Inst;
727 auto Duplex = HeadTail.first.split('\v');
728 if (!Duplex.second.empty()) {
729 OS << Duplex.first;
730 OS << "; ";
731 Inst = Duplex.second;
732 }
733 else
734 Inst = HeadTail.first;
735 OS << Inst;
736 HeadTail = HeadTail.second.split('\n');
737 if (HeadTail.first.empty())
738 OS << " } " << PacketBundle.second;
739 PrintReloc();
740 Bytes = Bytes.slice(4);
741 Address.Address += 4;
742 }
743 }
744};
745HexagonPrettyPrinter HexagonPrettyPrinterInst;
746
747class AMDGCNPrettyPrinter : public PrettyPrinter {
748public:
749 void printInst(MCInstPrinter &IP, const MCInst *MI, ArrayRef<uint8_t> Bytes,
750 object::SectionedAddress Address, raw_ostream &OS,
751 StringRef Annot, MCSubtargetInfo const &STI, SourcePrinter *SP,
752 std::vector<RelocationRef> *Rels) override {
753 if (SP && (PrintSource || PrintLines))
754 SP->printSourceLine(OS, Address);
755
756 typedef support::ulittle32_t U32;
757
758 if (MI) {
759 SmallString<40> InstStr;
760 raw_svector_ostream IS(InstStr);
761
762 IP.printInst(MI, IS, "", STI);
763
764 OS << left_justify(IS.str(), 60);
765 } else {
766 // an unrecognized encoding - this is probably data so represent it
767 // using the .long directive, or .byte directive if fewer than 4 bytes
768 // remaining
769 if (Bytes.size() >= 4) {
770 OS << format("\t.long 0x%08" PRIx32 " ",
771 static_cast<uint32_t>(*reinterpret_cast<const U32*>(Bytes.data())));
772 OS.indent(42);
773 } else {
774 OS << format("\t.byte 0x%02" PRIx8, Bytes[0]);
775 for (unsigned int i = 1; i < Bytes.size(); i++)
776 OS << format(", 0x%02" PRIx8, Bytes[i]);
777 OS.indent(55 - (6 * Bytes.size()));
778 }
779 }
780
781 OS << format("// %012" PRIX64 ": ", Address.Address);
782 if (Bytes.size() >=4) {
783 for (auto D : makeArrayRef(reinterpret_cast<const U32*>(Bytes.data()),
784 Bytes.size() / sizeof(U32)))
785 // D should be explicitly casted to uint32_t here as it is passed
786 // by format to snprintf as vararg.
787 OS << format("%08" PRIX32 " ", static_cast<uint32_t>(D));
788 } else {
789 for (unsigned int i = 0; i < Bytes.size(); i++)
790 OS << format("%02" PRIX8 " ", Bytes[i]);
791 }
792
793 if (!Annot.empty())
794 OS << "// " << Annot;
795 }
796};
797AMDGCNPrettyPrinter AMDGCNPrettyPrinterInst;
798
799class BPFPrettyPrinter : public PrettyPrinter {
800public:
801 void printInst(MCInstPrinter &IP, const MCInst *MI, ArrayRef<uint8_t> Bytes,
802 object::SectionedAddress Address, raw_ostream &OS,
803 StringRef Annot, MCSubtargetInfo const &STI, SourcePrinter *SP,
804 std::vector<RelocationRef> *Rels) override {
805 if (SP && (PrintSource || PrintLines))
806 SP->printSourceLine(OS, Address);
807 if (!NoLeadingAddr)
808 OS << format("%8" PRId64 ":", Address.Address / 8);
809 if (!NoShowRawInsn) {
810 OS << "\t";
811 dumpBytes(Bytes, OS);
812 }
813 if (MI)
814 IP.printInst(MI, OS, "", STI);
815 else
816 OS << "\t<unknown>";
817 }
818};
819BPFPrettyPrinter BPFPrettyPrinterInst;

822 switch(Triple.getArch()) {
823 default:
824 return PrettyPrinterInst;
825 case Triple::hexagon:
826 return HexagonPrettyPrinterInst;
827 case Triple::amdgcn:

829 case Triple::bpfel:
830 case Triple::bpfeb:

836static uint8_t getElfSymbolType(const ObjectFile *Obj, const SymbolRef &Sym) {
837 assert(Obj->isELF());
838 if (auto *Elf32LEObj = dyn_cast<ELF32LEObjectFile>(Obj))
839 return Elf32LEObj->getSymbol(Sym.getRawDataRefImpl())->getType();
840 if (auto *Elf64LEObj = dyn_cast<ELF64LEObjectFile>(Obj))
841 return Elf64LEObj->getSymbol(Sym.getRawDataRefImpl())->getType();
842 if (auto *Elf32BEObj = dyn_cast<ELF32BEObjectFile>(Obj))
843 return Elf32BEObj->getSymbol(Sym.getRawDataRefImpl())->getType();
844 if (auto *Elf64BEObj = cast<ELF64BEObjectFile>(Obj))
845 return Elf64BEObj->getSymbol(Sym.getRawDataRefImpl())->getType();
846 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported binary format");
847}
848
849template <class ELFT> static void
850addDynamicElfSymbols(const ELFObjectFile<ELFT> *Obj,
851 std::map<SectionRef, SectionSymbolsTy> &AllSymbols) {
852 for (auto Symbol : Obj->getDynamicSymbolIterators()) {
853 uint8_t SymbolType = Symbol.getELFType();
854 if (SymbolType != ELF::STT_FUNC || Symbol.getSize() == 0)
855 continue;
856
857 uint64_t Address = unwrapOrError(Symbol.getAddress(), Obj->getFileName());
858 StringRef Name = unwrapOrError(Symbol.getName(), Obj->getFileName());
859 if (Name.empty())
860 continue;
861
862 section_iterator SecI =
863 unwrapOrError(Symbol.getSection(), Obj->getFileName());
864 if (SecI == Obj->section_end())
865 continue;
866
867 AllSymbols[*SecI].emplace_back(Address, Name, SymbolType);
868 }
869}
870
871static void
872addDynamicElfSymbols(const ObjectFile *Obj,
873 std::map<SectionRef, SectionSymbolsTy> &AllSymbols) {
874 assert(Obj->isELF());
875 if (auto *Elf32LEObj = dyn_cast<ELF32LEObjectFile>(Obj))
876 addDynamicElfSymbols(Elf32LEObj, AllSymbols);
877 else if (auto *Elf64LEObj = dyn_cast<ELF64LEObjectFile>(Obj))
878 addDynamicElfSymbols(Elf64LEObj, AllSymbols);
879 else if (auto *Elf32BEObj = dyn_cast<ELF32BEObjectFile>(Obj))
880 addDynamicElfSymbols(Elf32BEObj, AllSymbols);
881 else if (auto *Elf64BEObj = cast<ELF64BEObjectFile>(Obj))
882 addDynamicElfSymbols(Elf64BEObj, AllSymbols);
883 else
884 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported binary format");
885}
886
887static void addPltEntries(const ObjectFile *Obj,
888 std::map<SectionRef, SectionSymbolsTy> &AllSymbols,
889 StringSaver &Saver) {
890 Optional<SectionRef> Plt = None;
891 for (const SectionRef &Section : Obj->sections()) {
892 StringRef Name;
893 if (Section.getName(Name))
894 continue;
895 if (Name == ".plt")
896 Plt = Section;
897 }
898 if (!Plt)
899 return;
900 if (auto *ElfObj = dyn_cast<ELFObjectFileBase>(Obj)) {
901 for (auto PltEntry : ElfObj->getPltAddresses()) {
902 SymbolRef Symbol(PltEntry.first, ElfObj);
903 uint8_t SymbolType = getElfSymbolType(Obj, Symbol);
904
905 StringRef Name = unwrapOrError(Symbol.getName(), Obj->getFileName());
906 if (!Name.empty())
907 AllSymbols[*Plt].emplace_back(
908 PltEntry.second, Saver.save((Name + "@plt").str()), SymbolType);
909 }
910 }
911}

913// Normally the disassembly output will skip blocks of zeroes. This function
914// returns the number of zero bytes that can be skipped when dumping the
915// disassembly of the instructions in Buf.
916static size_t countSkippableZeroBytes(ArrayRef<uint8_t> Buf) {
917 // Find the number of leading zeroes.
918 size_t N = 0;
919 while (N < Buf.size() && !Buf[N])
920 ++N;
921
922 // We may want to skip blocks of zero bytes, but unless we see
923 // at least 8 of them in a row.
924 if (N < 8)
925 return 0;
926
927 // We skip zeroes in multiples of 4 because do not want to truncate an
928 // instruction if it starts with a zero byte.
929 return N & ~0x3;
930}
931
932// Returns a map from sections to their relocations.
933static std::map<SectionRef, std::vector<RelocationRef>>
934getRelocsMap(object::ObjectFile const &Obj) {
935 std::map<SectionRef, std::vector<RelocationRef>> Ret;
936 for (SectionRef Sec : Obj.sections()) {
937 section_iterator Relocated = Sec.getRelocatedSection();
938 if (Relocated == Obj.section_end() || !shouldKeep(*Relocated))
939 continue;
940 std::vector<RelocationRef> &V = Ret[*Relocated];
941 for (const RelocationRef &R : Sec.relocations())
942 V.push_back(R);
943 // Sort relocations by address.
944 llvm::stable_sort(V, isRelocAddressLess);
945 }
946 return Ret;
947}

949// Used for --adjust-vma to check if address should be adjusted by the
950// specified value for a given section.
951// For ELF we do not adjust non-allocatable sections like debug ones,
952// because they are not loadable.
953// TODO: implement for other file formats.
954static bool shouldAdjustVA(const SectionRef &Section) {
955 const ObjectFile *Obj = Section.getObject();
956 if (isa<object::ELFObjectFileBase>(Obj))
957 return ELFSectionRef(Section).getFlags() & ELF::SHF_ALLOC;
958 return false;
959}

961static uint64_t
962dumpARMELFData(uint64_t SectionAddr, uint64_t Index, uint64_t End,
963 const ObjectFile *Obj, ArrayRef<uint8_t> Bytes,
964 const std::vector<uint64_t> &TextMappingSymsAddr) {
965 support::endianness Endian =
966 Obj->isLittleEndian() ? support::little : support::big;
967 while (Index < End) {
968 outs() << format("%8" PRIx64 ":", SectionAddr + Index);
969 outs() << "\t";
970 if (Index + 4 <= End) {
971 dumpBytes(Bytes.slice(Index, 4), outs());
972 outs() << "\t.word\t"
973 << format_hex(
974 support::endian::read32(Bytes.data() + Index, Endian), 10);
975 Index += 4;
976 } else if (Index + 2 <= End) {
977 dumpBytes(Bytes.slice(Index, 2), outs());
978 outs() << "\t\t.short\t"
979 << format_hex(
980 support::endian::read16(Bytes.data() + Index, Endian), 6);
981 Index += 2;
982 } else {
983 dumpBytes(Bytes.slice(Index, 1), outs());
984 outs() << "\t\t.byte\t" << format_hex(Bytes[0], 4);
985 ++Index;
986 }
987 outs() << "\n";
988 if (std::binary_search(TextMappingSymsAddr.begin(),
989 TextMappingSymsAddr.end(), Index))
990 break;
991 }
992 return Index;
993}
994
995static void dumpELFData(uint64_t SectionAddr, uint64_t Index, uint64_t End,
996 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Bytes) {
997 // print out data up to 8 bytes at a time in hex and ascii
998 uint8_t AsciiData[9] = {'\0'};
999 uint8_t Byte;
1000 int NumBytes = 0;
1001
1002 for (; Index < End; ++Index) {
1003 if (NumBytes == 0) {
1004 outs() << format("%8" PRIx64 ":", SectionAddr + Index);
1005 outs() << "\t";
1006 }
1007 Byte = Bytes.slice(Index)[0];
1008 outs() << format(" %02x", Byte);
1009 AsciiData[NumBytes] = isPrint(Byte) ? Byte : '.';
1010
1011 uint8_t IndentOffset = 0;
1012 NumBytes++;
1013 if (Index == End - 1 || NumBytes > 8) {
1014 // Indent the space for less than 8 bytes data.
1015 // 2 spaces for byte and one for space between bytes
1016 IndentOffset = 3 * (8 - NumBytes);
1017 for (int Excess = NumBytes; Excess < 8; Excess++)
1018 AsciiData[Excess] = '\0';
1019 NumBytes = 8;
1020 }
1021 if (NumBytes == 8) {
1022 AsciiData[8] = '\0';
1023 outs() << std::string(IndentOffset, ' ') << " ";
1024 outs() << reinterpret_cast<char *>(AsciiData);
1025 outs() << '\n';
1026 NumBytes = 0;
1027 }
1028 }
1029}
1030
1031static void disassembleObject(const Target *TheTarget, const ObjectFile *Obj,
1032 MCContext &Ctx, MCDisassembler *DisAsm,
1033 const MCInstrAnalysis *MIA, MCInstPrinter *IP,
1034 const MCSubtargetInfo *STI, PrettyPrinter &PIP,
1035 SourcePrinter &SP, bool InlineRelocs) {
1036 std::map<SectionRef, std::vector<RelocationRef>> RelocMap;
1037 if (InlineRelocs)
1038 RelocMap = getRelocsMap(*Obj);
1039
1040 llvm::Optional<uint64_t> CheriCapTableAddress;
1041
1042 // Create a mapping from virtual address to symbol name. This is used to
1043 // pretty print the symbols while disassembling.
1044 std::map<SectionRef, SectionSymbolsTy> AllSymbols;
1045 SectionSymbolsTy AbsoluteSymbols;
1046 const StringRef FileName = Obj->getFileName();
1047 for (const SymbolRef &Symbol : Obj->symbols()) {
1048 uint64_t Address = unwrapOrError(Symbol.getAddress(), FileName);
1049
1050 StringRef Name = unwrapOrError(Symbol.getName(), FileName);
1051 if (Name.empty())
1052 continue;
1053
1054 uint8_t SymbolType = ELF::STT_NOTYPE;
1055 if (Obj->isELF()) {
1056 SymbolType = getElfSymbolType(Obj, Symbol);
1057 if (SymbolType == ELF::STT_SECTION)
1058 continue;
1059 }
1060
1061 section_iterator SecI = unwrapOrError(Symbol.getSection(), FileName);
1062 if (SecI != Obj->section_end())
1063 AllSymbols[*SecI].emplace_back(Address, Name, SymbolType);
1064 else
1065 AbsoluteSymbols.emplace_back(Address, Name, SymbolType);
1066
1067 if (Name == "_CHERI_CAPABILITY_TABLE_") {
1068 // errs() << "FOUND CHERI CAP TABLE @" << utohexstr(Address);
1069 CheriCapTableAddress = Address;
1070 }
1071 }
1072 if (AllSymbols.empty() && Obj->isELF())
1073 addDynamicElfSymbols(Obj, AllSymbols);
1074
1075 BumpPtrAllocator A;
1076 StringSaver Saver(A);
1077 addPltEntries(Obj, AllSymbols, Saver);
1078
1079 // Create a mapping from virtual address to section.
1080 std::vector<std::pair<uint64_t, SectionRef>> SectionAddresses;
1081 for (SectionRef Sec : Obj->sections())
1082 SectionAddresses.emplace_back(Sec.getAddress(), Sec);
1083 array_pod_sort(SectionAddresses.begin(), SectionAddresses.end());
1084
1085 // Linked executables (.exe and .dll files) typically don't include a real
1086 // symbol table but they might contain an export table.
1087 if (const auto *COFFObj = dyn_cast<COFFObjectFile>(Obj)) {
1088 for (const auto &ExportEntry : COFFObj->export_directories()) {
1089 StringRef Name;
1090 error(ExportEntry.getSymbolName(Name));
1091 if (Name.empty())
1092 continue;
1093 uint32_t RVA;
1094 error(ExportEntry.getExportRVA(RVA));
1095
1096 uint64_t VA = COFFObj->getImageBase() + RVA;
1097 auto Sec = llvm::bsearch(
1098 SectionAddresses, [VA](const std::pair<uint64_t, SectionRef> &RHS) {
1099 return VA < RHS.first;
1100 });
1101 if (Sec != SectionAddresses.begin()) {
1102 --Sec;
1103 AllSymbols[Sec->second].emplace_back(VA, Name, ELF::STT_NOTYPE);
1104 } else
1105 AbsoluteSymbols.emplace_back(VA, Name, ELF::STT_NOTYPE);
1106 }
1107 }
1108
1109 // Sort all the symbols, this allows us to use a simple binary search to find
1110 // a symbol near an address.
1111 StringSet<> FoundDisasmFuncsSet;
1112 for (std::pair<const SectionRef, SectionSymbolsTy> &SecSyms : AllSymbols)
1113 array_pod_sort(SecSyms.second.begin(), SecSyms.second.end());
1114 array_pod_sort(AbsoluteSymbols.begin(), AbsoluteSymbols.end());
1115
1116 for (const SectionRef &Section : ToolSectionFilter(*Obj)) {
1117 if (FilterSections.empty() && !DisassembleAll &&
1118 (!Section.isText() || Section.isVirtual()))
1119 continue;
1120
1121 uint64_t SectionAddr = Section.getAddress();
1122 uint64_t SectSize = Section.getSize();
1123 if (!SectSize)
1124 continue;
1125
1126 // Get the list of all the symbols in this section.
1127 SectionSymbolsTy &Symbols = AllSymbols[Section];
1128 std::vector<uint64_t> DataMappingSymsAddr;
1129 std::vector<uint64_t> TextMappingSymsAddr;
1130 if (isArmElf(Obj)) {
1131 for (const auto &Symb : Symbols) {
1132 uint64_t Address = std::get<0>(Symb);
1133 StringRef Name = std::get<1>(Symb);
1134 if (Name.startswith("$d"))
1135 DataMappingSymsAddr.push_back(Address - SectionAddr);
1136 if (Name.startswith("$x"))
1137 TextMappingSymsAddr.push_back(Address - SectionAddr);
1138 if (Name.startswith("$a"))
1139 TextMappingSymsAddr.push_back(Address - SectionAddr);
1140 if (Name.startswith("$t"))
1141 TextMappingSymsAddr.push_back(Address - SectionAddr);
1142 }
1143 }
1144
1145 llvm::sort(DataMappingSymsAddr);
1146 llvm::sort(TextMappingSymsAddr);
1147
1148 if (Obj->isELF() && Obj->getArch() == Triple::amdgcn) {
1149 // AMDGPU disassembler uses symbolizer for printing labels
1150 std::unique_ptr<MCRelocationInfo> RelInfo(
1151 TheTarget->createMCRelocationInfo(TripleName, Ctx));
1152 if (RelInfo) {
1153 std::unique_ptr<MCSymbolizer> Symbolizer(
1154 TheTarget->createMCSymbolizer(
1155 TripleName, nullptr, nullptr, &Symbols, &Ctx, std::move(RelInfo)));
1156 DisAsm->setSymbolizer(std::move(Symbolizer));
1157 }
1158 }
1159
1160 StringRef SegmentName = "";
1161 if (const MachOObjectFile *MachO = dyn_cast<const MachOObjectFile>(Obj)) {
1162 DataRefImpl DR = Section.getRawDataRefImpl();
1163 SegmentName = MachO->getSectionFinalSegmentName(DR);
1164 }
1165 StringRef SectionName;
1166 error(Section.getName(SectionName));
1167
1168 // If the section has no symbol at the start, just insert a dummy one.
1169 if (Symbols.empty() || std::get<0>(Symbols[0]) != 0) {
1170 Symbols.insert(
1171 Symbols.begin(),
1172 std::make_tuple(SectionAddr, SectionName,
1173 Section.isText() ? ELF::STT_FUNC : ELF::STT_OBJECT));
1174 }
1175
1176 SmallString<40> Comments;
1177 raw_svector_ostream CommentStream(Comments);
1178
1179 ArrayRef<uint8_t> Bytes = arrayRefFromStringRef(
1180 unwrapOrError(Section.getContents(), Obj->getFileName()));
1181
1182 uint64_t VMAAdjustment = 0;
1183 if (shouldAdjustVA(Section))
1184 VMAAdjustment = AdjustVMA;
1185
1186 uint64_t Size = 0;
1187 uint64_t Index;
1188 bool PrintedSection = false;
1189 std::vector<RelocationRef> Rels = RelocMap[Section];
1190 std::vector<RelocationRef>::const_iterator RelCur = Rels.begin();
1191 std::vector<RelocationRef>::const_iterator RelEnd = Rels.end();
1192 // Disassemble symbol by symbol.
1193 for (unsigned SI = 0, SE = Symbols.size(); SI != SE; ++SI) {
1194 // Skip if --disassemble-functions is not empty and the symbol is not in
1195 // the list.
1196 if (!DisasmFuncsSet.empty() &&
1197 !DisasmFuncsSet.count(std::get<1>(Symbols[SI])))
1198 continue;
1199
1200 uint64_t Start = std::get<0>(Symbols[SI]);
1201 if (Start < SectionAddr || StopAddress <= Start)
1202 continue;
1203 else
1204 FoundDisasmFuncsSet.insert(std::get<1>(Symbols[SI]));
1205
1206 // The end is the section end, the beginning of the next symbol, or
1207 // --stop-address.
1208 uint64_t End = std::min<uint64_t>(SectionAddr + SectSize, StopAddress);
1209 if (SI + 1 < SE)
1210 End = std::min(End, std::get<0>(Symbols[SI + 1]));
1211 if (Start >= End || End <= StartAddress)
1212 continue;
1213 Start -= SectionAddr;
1214 End -= SectionAddr;
1215
1216 if (!PrintedSection) {
1217 PrintedSection = true;
1218 outs() << "\nDisassembly of section ";
1219 if (!SegmentName.empty())
1220 outs() << SegmentName << ",";
1221 outs() << SectionName << ":\n";
1222 }
1223
1224 if (Obj->isELF() && Obj->getArch() == Triple::amdgcn) {
1225 if (std::get<2>(Symbols[SI]) == ELF::STT_AMDGPU_HSA_KERNEL) {
1226 // skip amd_kernel_code_t at the begining of kernel symbol (256 bytes)
1227 Start += 256;
1228 }
1229 if (SI == SE - 1 ||
1230 std::get<2>(Symbols[SI + 1]) == ELF::STT_AMDGPU_HSA_KERNEL) {
1231 // cut trailing zeroes at the end of kernel
1232 // cut up to 256 bytes
1233 const uint64_t EndAlign = 256;
1234 const auto Limit = End - (std::min)(EndAlign, End - Start);
1235 while (End > Limit &&
1236 *reinterpret_cast<const support::ulittle32_t*>(&Bytes[End - 4]) == 0)
1237 End -= 4;
1238 }
1239 }
1240
1241 outs() << '\n';
1242 if (!NoLeadingAddr)
1243 outs() << format("%016" PRIx64 " ",
1244 SectionAddr + Start + VMAAdjustment);
1245
1246 StringRef SymbolName = std::get<1>(Symbols[SI]);
1247 if (Demangle)
1248 outs() << demangle(SymbolName) << ":\n";
1249 else
1250 outs() << SymbolName << ":\n";
1251
1252 // Don't print raw contents of a virtual section. A virtual section
1253 // doesn't have any contents in the file.
1254 if (Section.isVirtual()) {
1255 outs() << "...\n";
1256 continue;
1257 }
1258
1259#ifndef NDEBUG
1260 raw_ostream &DebugOut = DebugFlag ? dbgs() : nulls();
1261#else
1262 raw_ostream &DebugOut = nulls();
1263#endif
1264
1265 // Some targets (like WebAssembly) have a special prelude at the start
1266 // of each symbol.
1267 DisAsm->onSymbolStart(SymbolName, Size, Bytes.slice(Start, End - Start),
1268 SectionAddr + Start, DebugOut, CommentStream);
1269 Start += Size;
1270
1271 Index = Start;
1272 if (SectionAddr < StartAddress)
1273 Index = std::max<uint64_t>(Index, StartAddress - SectionAddr);
1274
1275 // If there is a data symbol inside an ELF text section and we are
1276 // only disassembling text (applicable all architectures), we are in a
1277 // situation where we must print the data and not disassemble it.
1278 if (Obj->isELF() && std::get<2>(Symbols[SI]) == ELF::STT_OBJECT &&
1279 !DisassembleAll && Section.isText()) {
1280 dumpELFData(SectionAddr, Index, End, Bytes);
1281 Index = End;
1282 }
1283
1284 bool CheckARMELFData = isArmElf(Obj) &&
1285 std::get<2>(Symbols[SI]) != ELF::STT_OBJECT &&
1286 !DisassembleAll;
1287 while (Index < End) {
1288 // AArch64 ELF binaries can interleave data and text in the same
1289 // section. We rely on the markers introduced to understand what we
1290 // need to dump. If the data marker is within a function, it is
1291 // denoted as a word/short etc.
1292 if (CheckARMELFData &&
1293 std::binary_search(DataMappingSymsAddr.begin(),
1294 DataMappingSymsAddr.end(), Index)) {
1295 Index = dumpARMELFData(SectionAddr, Index, End, Obj, Bytes,
1296 TextMappingSymsAddr);
1297 continue;
1298 }
1299
1300 // When -z or --disassemble-zeroes are given we always dissasemble
1301 // them. Otherwise we might want to skip zero bytes we see.
1302 if (!DisassembleZeroes) {
1303 uint64_t MaxOffset = End - Index;
1304 // For -reloc: print zero blocks patched by relocations, so that
1305 // relocations can be shown in the dump.
1306 if (RelCur != RelEnd)
1307 MaxOffset = RelCur->getOffset() - Index;
1308
1309 if (size_t N =
1310 countSkippableZeroBytes(Bytes.slice(Index, MaxOffset))) {
1311 outs() << "\t\t..." << '\n';
1312 Index += N;
1313 continue;
1314 }
1315 }
1316
1317 // Disassemble a real instruction or a data when disassemble all is
1318 // provided
1319 MCInst Inst;
1320 bool Disassembled = DisAsm->getInstruction(
1321 Inst, Size, Bytes.slice(Index), SectionAddr + Index, DebugOut,
1322 CommentStream);
1323 if (Size == 0)
1324 Size = 1;
1325
1326 PIP.printInst(
1327 *IP, Disassembled ? &Inst : nullptr, Bytes.slice(Index, Size),
1328 {SectionAddr + Index + VMAAdjustment, Section.getIndex()}, outs(),
1329 "", *STI, &SP, &Rels);
1330 outs() << CommentStream.str();
1331 Comments.clear();
1332
1333 // Try to resolve the target of a call, tail call, etc. to a specific
1334 // symbol.
1335 if (MIA && (MIA->isCall(Inst) || MIA->isUnconditionalBranch(Inst) ||
1336 MIA->isConditionalBranch(Inst))) {
1337 uint64_t Target;
1338 if (MIA->evaluateBranch(Inst, SectionAddr + Index, Size, Target)) {
1339 // In a relocatable object, the target's section must reside in
1340 // the same section as the call instruction or it is accessed
1341 // through a relocation.
1342 //
1343 // In a non-relocatable object, the target may be in any section.
1344 //
1345 // N.B. We don't walk the relocations in the relocatable case yet.
1346 auto *TargetSectionSymbols = &Symbols;
1347 if (!Obj->isRelocatableObject()) {
1348 auto It = llvm::bsearch(
1349 SectionAddresses,
1350 [=](const std::pair<uint64_t, SectionRef> &RHS) {
1351 return Target < RHS.first;
1352 });
1353 if (It != SectionAddresses.begin()) {
1354 --It;
1355 TargetSectionSymbols = &AllSymbols[It->second];
1356 } else {
1357 TargetSectionSymbols = &AbsoluteSymbols;
1358 }
1359 }
1360
1361 // Find the last symbol in the section whose offset is less than
1362 // or equal to the target. If there isn't a section that contains
1363 // the target, find the nearest preceding absolute symbol.
1364 auto TargetSym = llvm::bsearch(
1365 *TargetSectionSymbols,
1366 [=](const std::tuple<uint64_t, StringRef, uint8_t> &RHS) {
1367 return Target < std::get<0>(RHS);
1368 });
1369 if (TargetSym == TargetSectionSymbols->begin()) {
1370 TargetSectionSymbols = &AbsoluteSymbols;
1371 TargetSym = llvm::bsearch(
1372 AbsoluteSymbols,
1373 [=](const std::tuple<uint64_t, StringRef, uint8_t> &RHS) {
1374 return Target < std::get<0>(RHS);
1375 });
1376 }
1377 if (TargetSym != TargetSectionSymbols->begin()) {
1378 --TargetSym;
1379 uint64_t TargetAddress = std::get<0>(*TargetSym);
1380 StringRef TargetName = std::get<1>(*TargetSym);
1381 outs() << " <" << TargetName;
1382 uint64_t Disp = Target - TargetAddress;
1383 if (Disp)
1384 outs() << "+0x" << Twine::utohexstr(Disp);
1385 outs() << '>';
1386 }
1387 }
1388 }
1389
1390 // Add a comment which symbol is being loaded for cap-table loads
1391 int64_t CapTableOffset = std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::min();
1392 // In .o files we can just use -r to get useful results
1393 if (!Obj->isRelocatableObject() && MIA && CheriCapTableAddress &&
1394 MIA->isCapTableLoad(Inst, CapTableOffset)) {
1395
1396 uint64_t Target = *CheriCapTableAddress + CapTableOffset;
1397 // TODO: share this code:
1398
1399 // In a relocatable object, the target's section must reside in
1400 // the same section as the call instruction or it is accessed
1401 // through a relocation.
1402 //
1403 // In a non-relocatable object, the target may be in any section.
1404 //
1405 // N.B. We don't walk the relocations in the relocatable case yet.
1406 auto *TargetSectionSymbols = &Symbols;
1407 if (!Obj->isRelocatableObject()) {
1408 auto SectionAddress = std::upper_bound(
1409 SectionAddresses.begin(), SectionAddresses.end(), Target,
1410 [](uint64_t LHS, const std::pair<uint64_t, SectionRef> &RHS) {
1411 return LHS < RHS.first;
1412 });
1413 if (SectionAddress != SectionAddresses.begin()) {
1414 --SectionAddress;
1415 TargetSectionSymbols = &AllSymbols[SectionAddress->second];
1416 } else {
1417 TargetSectionSymbols = nullptr;
1418 }
1419 }
1420
1421 // Find the first symbol in the section whose offset is less than
1422 // or equal to the target.
1423 if (TargetSectionSymbols) {
1424 auto TargetSym = std::upper_bound(
1425 TargetSectionSymbols->begin(), TargetSectionSymbols->end(),
1426 Target,
1427 [](uint64_t LHS,
1428 const std::tuple<uint64_t, StringRef, uint8_t> &RHS) {
1429 return LHS < std::get<0>(RHS);
1430 });
1431 if (TargetSym != TargetSectionSymbols->begin()) {
1432 --TargetSym;
1433 uint64_t TargetAddress = std::get<0>(*TargetSym);
1434 StringRef TargetName = std::get<1>(*TargetSym);
1435 outs() << "\t# probably " << TargetName;
1436 uint64_t Disp = Target - TargetAddress;
1437 if (Disp)
1438 outs() << "+0x" << utohexstr(Disp);
1439 }
1440 }
1441 }
1442
1443 outs() << "\n";
1444
1445 // Hexagon does this in pretty printer
1446 if (Obj->getArch() != Triple::hexagon) {
1447 // Print relocation for instruction.
1448 while (RelCur != RelEnd) {
1449 uint64_t Offset = RelCur->getOffset();
1450 // If this relocation is hidden, skip it.
1451 if (getHidden(*RelCur) || SectionAddr + Offset < StartAddress) {
1452 ++RelCur;
1453 continue;
1454 }
1455
1456 // Stop when RelCur's offset is past the current instruction.
1457 if (Offset >= Index + Size)
1458 break;
1459
1460 // When --adjust-vma is used, update the address printed.
1461 if (RelCur->getSymbol() != Obj->symbol_end()) {
1462 Expected<section_iterator> SymSI =
1463 RelCur->getSymbol()->getSection();
1464 if (SymSI && *SymSI != Obj->section_end() &&
1465 shouldAdjustVA(**SymSI))
1466 Offset += AdjustVMA;
1467 }
1468
1469 printRelocation(*RelCur, SectionAddr + Offset,
1470 Obj->getBytesInAddress());
1471 ++RelCur;
1472 }
1473 }
1474
1475 Index += Size;
1476 }
1477 }
1478 }
1479 StringSet<> MissingDisasmFuncsSet =
1480 set_difference(DisasmFuncsSet, FoundDisasmFuncsSet);
1481 for (StringRef MissingDisasmFunc : MissingDisasmFuncsSet.keys())
1482 warn("failed to disassemble missing function " + MissingDisasmFunc);
1483}
1484
1485template <class ELFT> static void
1486printELFCapRelocations(const ELFObjectFile<ELFT> *Obj) {
1487 StringRef AddrFmt = Obj->getBytesInAddress() > 4 ? "0x%016" PRIx64 :
1488 "0x%08" PRIx64;
1489 StringRef PermsFmt = Obj->getBytesInAddress() > 4 ? "0x%08" PRIx64 :
1490 "0x%04" PRIx64;
1491
1492 std::unordered_map<uint64_t, std::string> SymbolNames;
1493 for (const SymbolRef &Sym : Obj->symbols()) {
1494 if (auto Type = Sym.getType()) {
1495 // Skip STT_FILE symbols
1496 if (*Type == SymbolRef::ST_File)
1497 continue;
1498 }
1499 auto Section = Sym.getSection();
1500 if (!Section || *Section == Obj->section_end()) {
1501 continue; // Skip undefined symbols
1502 }
1503 Expected<uint64_t> Start = Sym.getAddress();
1504 if (!Start)
1505 continue;
1506 Expected<StringRef> Name = Sym.getName();
1507 if (!Name) {
1508 continue;
1509 }
1510 SymbolNames.insert({Start.get(), Name.get().str()});
1511 }
1512 StringRef Data;
1513 for (const SectionRef &Sec : Obj->sections()) {
1514 StringRef Name;
1515 if (Sec.getName(Name))
1516 continue;
1517 if (Name == "__cap_relocs") {
1518 Data = unwrapOrError(Sec.getContents(), Obj->getFileName());
1519 break;
1520 }
1521 }
1522 outs() << "CAPABILITY RELOCATION RECORDS:\n";
1523 const size_t entry_size = ELFT::Is64Bits ? 40 : 20;
1524 using TargetUint = typename ELFT::uint;
1525 for (int i = 0, e = Data.size() / entry_size; i < e; i++) {
1526 const char *entry = Data.data() + (entry_size * i);
1527 uint64_t Target =
1528 support::endian::read<TargetUint, ELFT::TargetEndianness, 1>(
1529 entry);
1530 uint64_t Base =
1531 support::endian::read<TargetUint, ELFT::TargetEndianness, 1>(
1532 entry + sizeof(TargetUint));
1533 uint64_t Offset =
1534 support::endian::read<TargetUint, ELFT::TargetEndianness, 1>(
1535 entry + 2*sizeof(TargetUint));
1536 uint64_t Length =
1537 support::endian::read<TargetUint, ELFT::TargetEndianness, 1>(
1538 entry + 3*sizeof(TargetUint));
1539 uint64_t Perms =
1540 support::endian::read<TargetUint, ELFT::TargetEndianness, 1>(
1541 entry + 4*sizeof(TargetUint));
1542 bool isFunction = Perms & (UINT64_C(1) << ((sizeof(TargetUint) * 8) - 1));
1543 bool isConstant = Perms & (UINT64_C(1) << ((sizeof(TargetUint) * 8) - 2));
1544 //Perms &= 0xffffffff;
1545 StringRef Symbol = "<Unnamed symbol>";
1546 if (SymbolNames.find(Base) != SymbolNames.end())
1547 Symbol = SymbolNames[Base];
1548 outs() << format(AddrFmt.data(), Target) << "\tBase: " << Symbol << " ("
1549 << format(AddrFmt.data(), Base)
1550 << ")\tOffset: " << format(AddrFmt.data(), Offset)
1551 << "\tLength: " << format(AddrFmt.data(), Length)
1552 << "\tPermissions: " << format(PermsFmt.data(), Perms)
1553 << (isFunction ? " (Function)\n"
1554 : (isConstant ? " (Constant)\n" : "\n"));
1555 }
1556 outs() << "\n";
1557}
1558
1559void printCapRelocations(const ObjectFile *Obj) {
1560 if (!Obj->isELF()) {
1561 WithColor::error(errs(), ToolName)
1562 << "This operation is only currently supported "
1563 "for ELF object files.\n";
1564 return;
1565 }
1566
1567 if (auto *Elf32LEObj = dyn_cast<ELF32LEObjectFile>(Obj))
1568 printELFCapRelocations(Elf32LEObj);
1569 else if (auto *Elf64LEObj = dyn_cast<ELF64LEObjectFile>(Obj))
1570 printELFCapRelocations(Elf64LEObj);
1571 else if (auto *Elf32BEObj = dyn_cast<ELF32BEObjectFile>(Obj))
1572 printELFCapRelocations(Elf32BEObj);
1573 else if (auto *Elf64BEObj = cast<ELF64BEObjectFile>(Obj))
1574 printELFCapRelocations(Elf64BEObj);
1575 else
1576 llvm_unreachable("Unsupported binary format");
1577}
1578
1579static void disassembleObject(const ObjectFile *Obj, bool InlineRelocs) {
1580 if (StartAddress >= StopAddress)
1581 error("start address should be less than stop address");
1582
1583 const Target *TheTarget = getTarget(Obj);
1584
1585 // Package up features to be passed to target/subtarget
1586 SubtargetFeatures Features = Obj->getFeatures();
1587 if (!MAttrs.empty())
1588 for (unsigned I = 0; I != MAttrs.size(); ++I)
1589 Features.AddFeature(MAttrs[I]);
1590
1591 std::unique_ptr<const MCRegisterInfo> MRI(
1592 TheTarget->createMCRegInfo(TripleName));
1593 if (!MRI)
1594 report_error(Obj->getFileName(),
1595 "no register info for target " + TripleName);
1596
1597 // Set up disassembler.
1598 std::unique_ptr<const MCAsmInfo> AsmInfo(
1599 TheTarget->createMCAsmInfo(*MRI, TripleName));
1600 if (!AsmInfo)
1601 report_error(Obj->getFileName(),
1602 "no assembly info for target " + TripleName);
1603 std::unique_ptr<const MCSubtargetInfo> STI(
1604 TheTarget->createMCSubtargetInfo(TripleName, MCPU, Features.getString()));
1605 if (!STI)
1606 report_error(Obj->getFileName(),
1607 "no subtarget info for target " + TripleName);
1608 std::unique_ptr<const MCInstrInfo> MII(TheTarget->createMCInstrInfo());
1609 if (!MII)
1610 report_error(Obj->getFileName(),
1611 "no instruction info for target " + TripleName);
1612 MCObjectFileInfo MOFI;
1613 MCContext Ctx(AsmInfo.get(), MRI.get(), &MOFI);
1614 // FIXME: for now initialize MCObjectFileInfo with default values
1615 MOFI.InitMCObjectFileInfo(Triple(TripleName), false, Ctx);
1616
1617 std::unique_ptr<MCDisassembler> DisAsm(
1618 TheTarget->createMCDisassembler(*STI, Ctx));
1619 if (!DisAsm)
1620 report_error(Obj->getFileName(),
1621 "no disassembler for target " + TripleName);
1622
1623 std::unique_ptr<const MCInstrAnalysis> MIA(
1624 TheTarget->createMCInstrAnalysis(MII.get()));
1625
1626 int AsmPrinterVariant = AsmInfo->getAssemblerDialect();
1627 std::unique_ptr<MCInstPrinter> IP(TheTarget->createMCInstPrinter(
1628 Triple(TripleName), AsmPrinterVariant, *AsmInfo, *MII, *MRI));
1629 if (!IP)
1630 report_error(Obj->getFileName(),
1631 "no instruction printer for target " + TripleName);
1632 IP->setPrintImmHex(PrintImmHex);
1633
1634 PrettyPrinter &PIP = selectPrettyPrinter(Triple(TripleName));
1635 SourcePrinter SP(Obj, TheTarget->getName());
1636
1637 for (StringRef Opt : DisassemblerOptions)
1638 if (!IP->applyTargetSpecificCLOption(Opt))
1639 error("Unrecognized disassembler option: " + Opt);
1640
1641 disassembleObject(TheTarget, Obj, Ctx, DisAsm.get(), MIA.get(), IP.get(),
1642 STI.get(), PIP, SP, InlineRelocs);
1643}
1644
1645void printRelocations(const ObjectFile *Obj) {
1646 StringRef Fmt = Obj->getBytesInAddress() > 4 ? "%016" PRIx64 :
1647 "%08" PRIx64;
1648 // Regular objdump doesn't print relocations in non-relocatable object
1649 // files.
1650 if (!Obj->isRelocatableObject())
1651 return;
1652
1653 // Build a mapping from relocation target to a vector of relocation
1654 // sections. Usually, there is an only one relocation section for
1655 // each relocated section.
1656 MapVector<SectionRef, std::vector<SectionRef>> SecToRelSec;
1657 for (const SectionRef &Section : ToolSectionFilter(*Obj)) {
1658 if (Section.relocation_begin() == Section.relocation_end())
1659 continue;
1660 const SectionRef TargetSec = *Section.getRelocatedSection();
1661 SecToRelSec[TargetSec].push_back(Section);
1662 }
1663
1664 for (std::pair<SectionRef, std::vector<SectionRef>> &P : SecToRelSec) {
1665 StringRef SecName;
1666 error(P.first.getName(SecName));
1667 outs() << "RELOCATION RECORDS FOR [" << SecName << "]:\n";
1668
1669 for (SectionRef Section : P.second) {
1670 for (const RelocationRef &Reloc : Section.relocations()) {
1671 uint64_t Address = Reloc.getOffset();
1672 SmallString<32> RelocName;
1673 SmallString<32> ValueStr;
1674 if (Address < StartAddress || Address > StopAddress || getHidden(Reloc))
1675 continue;
1676 Reloc.getTypeName(RelocName);
1677 error(getRelocationValueString(Reloc, ValueStr));
1678 outs() << format(Fmt.data(), Address) << " " << RelocName << " "
1679 << ValueStr << "\n";
1680 }
1681 }
1682 outs() << "\n";
1683 }
1684}
1685
1686void printDynamicRelocations(const ObjectFile *Obj) {
1687 // For the moment, this option is for ELF only
1688 if (!Obj->isELF())
1689 return;
1690
1691 const auto *Elf = dyn_cast<ELFObjectFileBase>(Obj);
1692 if (!Elf || Elf->getEType() != ELF::ET_DYN) {
1693 error("not a dynamic object");
1694 return;
1695 }
1696
1697 std::vector<SectionRef> DynRelSec = Obj->dynamic_relocation_sections();
1698 if (DynRelSec.empty())
1699 return;
1700
1701 outs() << "DYNAMIC RELOCATION RECORDS\n";
1702 StringRef Fmt = Obj->getBytesInAddress() > 4 ? "%016" PRIx64 : "%08" PRIx64;
1703 for (const SectionRef &Section : DynRelSec)
1704 for (const RelocationRef &Reloc : Section.relocations()) {
1705 uint64_t Address = Reloc.getOffset();
1706 SmallString<32> RelocName;
1707 SmallString<32> ValueStr;
1708 Reloc.getTypeName(RelocName);
1709 error(getRelocationValueString(Reloc, ValueStr));
1710 outs() << format(Fmt.data(), Address) << " " << RelocName << " "
1711 << ValueStr << "\n";
1712 }
1713}

1715// Returns true if we need to show LMA column when dumping section headers. We
1716// show it only when the platform is ELF and either we have at least one section
1717// whose VMA and LMA are different and/or when --show-lma flag is used.
1718static bool shouldDisplayLMA(const ObjectFile *Obj) {
1719 if (!Obj->isELF())
1720 return false;
1721 for (const SectionRef &S : ToolSectionFilter(*Obj))
1722 if (S.getAddress() != getELFSectionLMA(S))
1723 return true;
1724 return ShowLMA;
1725}
1726
1727void printSectionHeaders(const ObjectFile *Obj) {
1728 bool HasLMAColumn = shouldDisplayLMA(Obj);
1729 if (HasLMAColumn)
1730 outs() << "Sections:\n"
1731 "Idx Name Size VMA LMA "
1732 "Type\n";
1733 else
1734 outs() << "Sections:\n"
1735 "Idx Name Size VMA Type\n";
1736
1737 for (const SectionRef &Section : ToolSectionFilter(*Obj)) {
1738 StringRef Name;
1739 error(Section.getName(Name));
1740 uint64_t VMA = Section.getAddress();
1741 if (shouldAdjustVA(Section))
1742 VMA += AdjustVMA;
1743
1744 uint64_t Size = Section.getSize();
1745 bool Text = Section.isText();
1746 bool Data = Section.isData();
1747 bool BSS = Section.isBSS();
1748 std::string Type = (std::string(Text ? "TEXT " : "") +
1749 (Data ? "DATA " : "") + (BSS ? "BSS" : ""));
1750
1751 if (HasLMAColumn)
1752 outs() << format("%3d %-13s %08" PRIx64 " %016" PRIx64 " %016" PRIx64
1753 " %s\n",
1754 (unsigned)Section.getIndex(), Name.str().c_str(), Size,
1755 VMA, getELFSectionLMA(Section), Type.c_str());
1756 else
1757 outs() << format("%3d %-13s %08" PRIx64 " %016" PRIx64 " %s\n",
1758 (unsigned)Section.getIndex(), Name.str().c_str(), Size,
1759 VMA, Type.c_str());
1760 }
1761 outs() << "\n";
1762}
1763
1764void printSectionContents(const ObjectFile *Obj) {
1765 for (const SectionRef &Section : ToolSectionFilter(*Obj)) {
1766 StringRef Name;
1767 error(Section.getName(Name));
1768 uint64_t BaseAddr = Section.getAddress();
1769 uint64_t Size = Section.getSize();
1770 if (!Size)
1771 continue;
1772
1773 outs() << "Contents of section " << Name << ":\n";
1774 if (Section.isBSS()) {
1775 outs() << format("<skipping contents of bss section at [%04" PRIx64
1776 ", %04" PRIx64 ")>\n",
1777 BaseAddr, BaseAddr + Size);
1778 continue;
1779 }
1780
1781 StringRef Contents = unwrapOrError(Section.getContents(), Obj->getFileName());
1782
1783 // Dump out the content as hex and printable ascii characters.
1784 for (std::size_t Addr = 0, End = Contents.size(); Addr < End; Addr += 16) {
1785 outs() << format(" %04" PRIx64 " ", BaseAddr + Addr);
1786 // Dump line of hex.
1787 for (std::size_t I = 0; I < 16; ++I) {
1788 if (I != 0 && I % 4 == 0)
1789 outs() << ' ';
1790 if (Addr + I < End)
1791 outs() << hexdigit((Contents[Addr + I] >> 4) & 0xF, true)
1792 << hexdigit(Contents[Addr + I] & 0xF, true);
1793 else
1794 outs() << " ";
1795 }
1796 // Print ascii.
1797 outs() << " ";
1798 for (std::size_t I = 0; I < 16 && Addr + I < End; ++I) {
1799 if (isPrint(static_cast<unsigned char>(Contents[Addr + I]) & 0xFF))
1800 outs() << Contents[Addr + I];
1801 else
1802 outs() << ".";
1803 }
1804 outs() << "\n";
1805 }
1806 }
1807}
1808
1809void printSymbolTable(const ObjectFile *O, StringRef ArchiveName,
1810 StringRef ArchitectureName) {
1811 outs() << "SYMBOL TABLE:\n";
1812
1813 if (const COFFObjectFile *Coff = dyn_cast<const COFFObjectFile>(O)) {
1814 printCOFFSymbolTable(Coff);
1815 return;
1816 }
1817
1818 const StringRef FileName = O->getFileName();
1819 for (auto I = O->symbol_begin(), E = O->symbol_end(); I != E; ++I) {
1820 const SymbolRef &Symbol = *I;
1821 uint64_t Address = unwrapOrError(Symbol.getAddress(), ArchiveName, FileName,
1822 ArchitectureName);
1823 if ((Address < StartAddress) || (Address > StopAddress))
1824 continue;
1825 SymbolRef::Type Type = unwrapOrError(Symbol.getType(), ArchiveName,
1826 FileName, ArchitectureName);
1827 uint32_t Flags = Symbol.getFlags();
1828 section_iterator Section = unwrapOrError(Symbol.getSection(), ArchiveName,
1829 FileName, ArchitectureName);
1830 StringRef Name;
1831 if (Type == SymbolRef::ST_Debug && Section != O->section_end())
1832 Section->getName(Name);
1833 else
1834 Name = unwrapOrError(Symbol.getName(), ArchiveName, FileName,
1835 ArchitectureName);
1836
1837 bool Global = Flags & SymbolRef::SF_Global;
1838 bool Weak = Flags & SymbolRef::SF_Weak;
1839 bool Absolute = Flags & SymbolRef::SF_Absolute;
1840 bool Common = Flags & SymbolRef::SF_Common;
1841 bool Hidden = Flags & SymbolRef::SF_Hidden;
1842
1843 char GlobLoc = ' ';
1844 if (Type != SymbolRef::ST_Unknown)
1845 GlobLoc = Global ? 'g' : 'l';
1846 char Debug = (Type == SymbolRef::ST_Debug || Type == SymbolRef::ST_File)
1847 ? 'd' : ' ';
1848 char FileFunc = ' ';
1849 if (Type == SymbolRef::ST_File)
1850 FileFunc = 'f';
1851 else if (Type == SymbolRef::ST_Function)
1852 FileFunc = 'F';
1853 else if (Type == SymbolRef::ST_Data)
1854 FileFunc = 'O';
1855
1856 const char *Fmt = O->getBytesInAddress() > 4 ? "%016" PRIx64 :
1857 "%08" PRIx64;
1858
1859 outs() << format(Fmt, Address) << " "
1860 << GlobLoc // Local -> 'l', Global -> 'g', Neither -> ' '
1861 << (Weak ? 'w' : ' ') // Weak?
1862 << ' ' // Constructor. Not supported yet.
1863 << ' ' // Warning. Not supported yet.
1864 << ' ' // Indirect reference to another symbol.
1865 << Debug // Debugging (d) or dynamic (D) symbol.
1866 << FileFunc // Name of function (F), file (f) or object (O).
1867 << ' ';
1868 if (Absolute) {
1869 outs() << "*ABS*";
1870 } else if (Common) {
1871 outs() << "*COM*";
1872 } else if (Section == O->section_end()) {
1873 outs() << "*UND*";
1874 } else {
1875 if (const MachOObjectFile *MachO =
1876 dyn_cast<const MachOObjectFile>(O)) {
1877 DataRefImpl DR = Section->getRawDataRefImpl();
1878 StringRef SegmentName = MachO->getSectionFinalSegmentName(DR);
1879 outs() << SegmentName << ",";
1880 }
1881 StringRef SectionName;
1882 error(Section->getName(SectionName));
1883 outs() << SectionName;
1884 }
1885
1886 if (Common || isa<ELFObjectFileBase>(O)) {
1887 uint64_t Val =
1888 Common ? Symbol.getAlignment() : ELFSymbolRef(Symbol).getSize();
1889 outs() << format("\t%08" PRIx64, Val);
1890 }
1891
1892 if (isa<ELFObjectFileBase>(O)) {
1893 uint8_t Other = ELFSymbolRef(Symbol).getOther();
1894 switch (Other) {
1895 case ELF::STV_DEFAULT:
1896 break;
1897 case ELF::STV_INTERNAL:
1898 outs() << " .internal";
1899 break;
1900 case ELF::STV_HIDDEN:
1901 outs() << " .hidden";
1902 break;
1903 case ELF::STV_PROTECTED:
1904 outs() << " .protected";
1905 break;
1906 default:
1907 outs() << format(" 0x%02x", Other);
1908 break;
1909 }
1910 } else if (Hidden) {
1911 outs() << " .hidden";
1912 }
1913
1914 if (Demangle)
1915 outs() << ' ' << demangle(Name) << '\n';
1916 else
1917 outs() << ' ' << Name << '\n';
1918 }
1919}

1921static void printUnwindInfo(const ObjectFile *O) {
1922 outs() << "Unwind info:\n\n";
1923
1924 if (const COFFObjectFile *Coff = dyn_cast<COFFObjectFile>(O))
1925 printCOFFUnwindInfo(Coff);
1926 else if (const MachOObjectFile *MachO = dyn_cast<MachOObjectFile>(O))
1927 printMachOUnwindInfo(MachO);
1928 else
1929 // TODO: Extract DWARF dump tool to objdump.
1930 WithColor::error(errs(), ToolName)
1931 << "This operation is only currently supported "
1932 "for COFF and MachO object files.\n";
1933}

1935/// Dump the raw contents of the __clangast section so the output can be piped
1936/// into llvm-bcanalyzer.
1937void printRawClangAST(const ObjectFile *Obj) {
1938 if (outs().is_displayed()) {
1939 WithColor::error(errs(), ToolName)
1940 << "The -raw-clang-ast option will dump the raw binary contents of "
1941 "the clang ast section.\n"
1942 "Please redirect the output to a file or another program such as "
1943 "llvm-bcanalyzer.\n";
1944 return;
1945 }
1946
1947 StringRef ClangASTSectionName("__clangast");
1948 if (isa<COFFObjectFile>(Obj)) {
1949 ClangASTSectionName = "clangast";
1950 }
1951
1952 Optional<object::SectionRef> ClangASTSection;
1953 for (auto Sec : ToolSectionFilter(*Obj)) {
1954 StringRef Name;
1955 Sec.getName(Name);
1956 if (Name == ClangASTSectionName) {
1957 ClangASTSection = Sec;
1958 break;
1959 }
1960 }
1961 if (!ClangASTSection)
1962 return;
1963
1964 StringRef ClangASTContents = unwrapOrError(
1965 ClangASTSection.getValue().getContents(), Obj->getFileName());
1966 outs().write(ClangASTContents.data(), ClangASTContents.size());
1967}

1969static void printFaultMaps(const ObjectFile *Obj) {
1970 StringRef FaultMapSectionName;
1971
1972 if (isa<ELFObjectFileBase>(Obj)) {
1973 FaultMapSectionName = ".llvm_faultmaps";
1974 } else if (isa<MachOObjectFile>(Obj)) {
1975 FaultMapSectionName = "__llvm_faultmaps";
1976 } else {
1977 WithColor::error(errs(), ToolName)
1978 << "This operation is only currently supported "
1979 "for ELF and Mach-O executable files.\n";
1980 return;
1981 }
1982
1983 Optional<object::SectionRef> FaultMapSection;
1984
1985 for (auto Sec : ToolSectionFilter(*Obj)) {
1986 StringRef Name;
1987 Sec.getName(Name);
1988 if (Name == FaultMapSectionName) {
1989 FaultMapSection = Sec;
1990 break;
1991 }
1992 }
1993
1994 outs() << "FaultMap table:\n";
1995
1996 if (!FaultMapSection.hasValue()) {
1997 outs() << "<not found>\n";
1998 return;
1999 }
2000
2001 StringRef FaultMapContents =
2002 unwrapOrError(FaultMapSection.getValue().getContents(), Obj->getFileName());
2003 FaultMapParser FMP(FaultMapContents.bytes_begin(),
2004 FaultMapContents.bytes_end());
2005
2006 outs() << FMP;
2007}

2010 if (O->isELF()) {

2029static void printFileHeaders(const ObjectFile *O) {
2030 if (!O->isELF() && !O->isCOFF())
2031 report_error(O->getFileName(), "Invalid/Unsupported object file format");
2032
2033 Triple::ArchType AT = O->getArch();
2034 outs() << "architecture: " << Triple::getArchTypeName(AT) << "\n";
2035 uint64_t Address = unwrapOrError(O->getStartAddress(), O->getFileName());
2036
2037 StringRef Fmt = O->getBytesInAddress() > 4 ? "%016" PRIx64 : "%08" PRIx64;
2038 outs() << "start address: "
2039 << "0x" << format(Fmt.data(), Address) << "\n\n";
2040}

2042static void printArchiveChild(StringRef Filename, const Archive::Child &C) {
2043 Expected<sys::fs::perms> ModeOrErr = C.getAccessMode();
2044 if (!ModeOrErr) {
2045 WithColor::error(errs(), ToolName) << "ill-formed archive entry.\n";
2046 consumeError(ModeOrErr.takeError());
2047 return;
2048 }
2049 sys::fs::perms Mode = ModeOrErr.get();
2050 outs() << ((Mode & sys::fs::owner_read) ? "r" : "-");
2051 outs() << ((Mode & sys::fs::owner_write) ? "w" : "-");
2052 outs() << ((Mode & sys::fs::owner_exe) ? "x" : "-");
2053 outs() << ((Mode & sys::fs::group_read) ? "r" : "-");
2054 outs() << ((Mode & sys::fs::group_write) ? "w" : "-");
2055 outs() << ((Mode & sys::fs::group_exe) ? "x" : "-");
2056 outs() << ((Mode & sys::fs::others_read) ? "r" : "-");
2057 outs() << ((Mode & sys::fs::others_write) ? "w" : "-");
2058 outs() << ((Mode & sys::fs::others_exe) ? "x" : "-");
2059
2060 outs() << " ";
2061
2062 outs() << format("%d/%d %6" PRId64 " ", unwrapOrError(C.getUID(), Filename),
2063 unwrapOrError(C.getGID(), Filename),
2064 unwrapOrError(C.getRawSize(), Filename));
2065
2066 StringRef RawLastModified = C.getRawLastModified();
2067 unsigned Seconds;
2068 if (RawLastModified.getAsInteger(10, Seconds))
2069 outs() << "(date: \"" << RawLastModified
2070 << "\" contains non-decimal chars) ";
2071 else {
2072 // Since ctime(3) returns a 26 character string of the form:
2073 // "Sun Sep 16 01:03:52 1973\n\0"
2074 // just print 24 characters.
2075 time_t t = Seconds;
2076 outs() << format("%.24s ", ctime(&t));
2077 }
2078
2079 StringRef Name = "";
2080 Expected<StringRef> NameOrErr = C.getName();
2081 if (!NameOrErr) {
2082 consumeError(NameOrErr.takeError());
2083 Name = unwrapOrError(C.getRawName(), Filename);
2084 } else {
2085 Name = NameOrErr.get();
2086 }
2087 outs() << Name << "\n";
2088}

2090static void dumpObject(ObjectFile *O, const Archive *A = nullptr,
2091 const Archive::Child *C = nullptr) {
2092 // Avoid other output when using a raw option.
2093 if (!RawClangAST) {
2094 outs() << '\n';
2095 if (A)
2096 outs() << A->getFileName() << "(" << O->getFileName() << ")";
2097 else
2098 outs() << O->getFileName();
2099 outs() << ":\tfile format " << O->getFileFormatName() << "\n\n";
2100 }
2101
2102 StringRef ArchiveName = A ? A->getFileName() : "";
2103 if (FileHeaders)
2104 printFileHeaders(O);
2105 if (ArchiveHeaders && !MachOOpt && C)
2106 printArchiveChild(ArchiveName, *C);
2107 if (Disassemble)
2108 disassembleObject(O, Relocations);
2109 if (Relocations && !Disassemble)
2110 printRelocations(O);
2111 if (CapRelocations)
2112 printCapRelocations(O);
2113 if (DynamicRelocations)
2114 printDynamicRelocations(O);
2115 if (SectionHeaders)
2116 printSectionHeaders(O);
2117 if (SectionContents)
2118 printSectionContents(O);
2119 if (SymbolTable)
2120 printSymbolTable(O, ArchiveName);
2121 if (UnwindInfo)
2122 printUnwindInfo(O);
2123 if (PrivateHeaders || FirstPrivateHeader)
2124 printPrivateFileHeaders(O, FirstPrivateHeader);
2125 if (ExportsTrie)
2126 printExportsTrie(O);
2127 if (Rebase)
2128 printRebaseTable(O);
2129 if (Bind)
2130 printBindTable(O);
2131 if (LazyBind)
2132 printLazyBindTable(O);
2133 if (WeakBind)
2134 printWeakBindTable(O);
2135 if (RawClangAST)
2136 printRawClangAST(O);
2137 if (FaultMapSection)
2138 printFaultMaps(O);
2139 if (DwarfDumpType != DIDT_Null) {
2140 std::unique_ptr<DIContext> DICtx = DWARFContext::create(*O);
2141 // Dump the complete DWARF structure.
2142 DIDumpOptions DumpOpts;
2143 DumpOpts.DumpType = DwarfDumpType;
2144 DICtx->dump(outs(), DumpOpts);
2145 }
2146}

2148static void dumpObject(const COFFImportFile *I, const Archive *A,
2149 const Archive::Child *C = nullptr) {
2150 StringRef ArchiveName = A ? A->getFileName() : "";
2151
2152 // Avoid other output when using a raw option.
2153 if (!RawClangAST)
2154 outs() << '\n'
2155 << ArchiveName << "(" << I->getFileName() << ")"
2156 << ":\tfile format COFF-import-file"
2157 << "\n\n";
2158
2159 if (ArchiveHeaders && !MachOOpt && C)
2160 printArchiveChild(ArchiveName, *C);
2161 if (SymbolTable)

2165/// Dump each object file in \a a;
2166static void dumpArchive(const Archive *A) {
2167 Error Err = Error::success();
2168 for (auto &C : A->children(Err)) {
2169 Expected<std::unique_ptr<Binary>> ChildOrErr = C.getAsBinary();
2170 if (!ChildOrErr) {
2171 if (auto E = isNotObjectErrorInvalidFileType(ChildOrErr.takeError()))
2172 report_error(std::move(E), A->getFileName(), C);
2173 continue;
2174 }
2175 if (ObjectFile *O = dyn_cast<ObjectFile>(&*ChildOrErr.get()))
2176 dumpObject(O, A, &C);
2177 else if (COFFImportFile *I = dyn_cast<COFFImportFile>(&*ChildOrErr.get()))
2178 dumpObject(I, A, &C);
2179 else
2180 report_error(errorCodeToError(object_error::invalid_file_type),
2181 A->getFileName());
2182 }
2183 if (Err)
2184 report_error(std::move(Err), A->getFileName());
2185}

2187/// Open file and figure out how to dump it.
2188static void dumpInput(StringRef file) {
2189 // If we are using the Mach-O specific object file parser, then let it parse
2190 // the file and process the command line options. So the -arch flags can
2191 // be used to select specific slices, etc.
2192 if (MachOOpt) {
2193 parseInputMachO(file);
2194 return;
2195 }
2196
2197 // Attempt to open the binary.
2198 OwningBinary<Binary> OBinary = unwrapOrError(createBinary(file), file);
2199 Binary &Binary = *OBinary.getBinary();
2200
2201 if (Archive *A = dyn_cast<Archive>(&Binary))
2202 dumpArchive(A);
2203 else if (ObjectFile *O = dyn_cast<ObjectFile>(&Binary))
2204 dumpObject(O);
2205 else if (MachOUniversalBinary *UB = dyn_cast<MachOUniversalBinary>(&Binary))
2206 parseInputMachO(UB);
2207 else
2208 report_error(errorCodeToError(object_error::invalid_file_type), file);
2209}

2212int main(int argc, char **argv) {
2213 using namespace llvm;
2214 InitLLVM X(argc, argv);
2215 const cl::OptionCategory *OptionFilters[] = {&ObjdumpCat, &MachOCat};
2216 cl::HideUnrelatedOptions(OptionFilters);
2217
2218 // Initialize targets and assembly printers/parsers.
2219 InitializeAllTargetInfos();
2220 InitializeAllTargetMCs();
2221 InitializeAllDisassemblers();
2222
2223 // Register the target printer for --version.
2224 cl::AddExtraVersionPrinter(TargetRegistry::printRegisteredTargetsForVersion);
2225
2226 cl::ParseCommandLineOptions(argc, argv, "llvm object file dumper\n");
2227
2228 ToolName = argv[0];
2229
2230 // Defaults to a.out if no filenames specified.
2231 if (InputFilenames.empty())
2232 InputFilenames.push_back("a.out");
2233
2234 if (AllHeaders)
2235 ArchiveHeaders = FileHeaders = PrivateHeaders = Relocations =
2236 SectionHeaders = SymbolTable = true;
2237
2238 if (DisassembleAll || PrintSource || PrintLines ||
2239 (!DisassembleFunctions.empty()))
2240 Disassemble = true;
2241
2242 if (!ArchiveHeaders && !Disassemble && DwarfDumpType == DIDT_Null && !CapRelocations &&
2243 !DynamicRelocations && !FileHeaders && !PrivateHeaders && !RawClangAST &&
2244 !Relocations && !SectionHeaders && !SectionContents && !SymbolTable &&
2245 !UnwindInfo && !FaultMapSection &&
2246 !(MachOOpt &&
2247 (Bind || DataInCode || DylibId || DylibsUsed || ExportsTrie ||
2248 FirstPrivateHeader || IndirectSymbols || InfoPlist || LazyBind ||
2249 LinkOptHints || ObjcMetaData || Rebase || UniversalHeaders ||
2250 WeakBind || !FilterSections.empty()))) {
2251 cl::PrintHelpMessage();
2252 return 2;
2253 }
2254
2255 DisasmFuncsSet.insert(DisassembleFunctions.begin(),
2256 DisassembleFunctions.end());
2257
2258 llvm::for_each(InputFilenames, dumpInput);
2259
2260 return EXIT_SUCCESS;
2261}
